# Loop through each dataframe in the list
for (i in seq_along(queries)) {
  # Access the dataframe
  prj[["base"]][[queries[i]]][["scenario"]] <- "Reference"
  prj[["nz11march"]][[queries[i]]][["scenario"]] <- "Net_Zero"
}

gdp <- getQuery(prj, "GDP by region") %>% mutate(category = "GDP")
pop <- getQuery(prj, "Population by region") %>% mutate(category = "Pop")
gdpPc <- getQuery(prj, "PPP GDP by region") %>% mutate(category = "GDPPC")

socioeco <- bind_rows(gdp, pop, gdpPc) # %>% filter(scenario=="BAU_GJ")

ggplot(socioeco %>% filter(region %in% c("UK", "TN", "KA", "MH"), category == "Pop", year > 2005, year < 2075, scenario == "Reference"), mapping = aes(x = year, y = value / 1e3, color = region)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_point(shape = "circle", size = 2) +
  geom_label_repel(socioeco %>% filter(region %in% c("UK", "TN", "KA", "MH"), category == "Pop", year == 2070, scenario == "Reference"),
    mapping = aes(x = year, y = value / 1e3, color = region, label = region),
    nudge_x = 6, box.padding = 0.3, direction = "y",
    na.rm = TRUE, show.legend = F, force_pull = 0.5
  ) +
  geom_line() + # Divide by 1e6 to convert to millions

  scale_color_aaas() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2010, 2070, by = 10)) +
  guides(color = "none") +
  labs(y = "Population (Millions)", x = "")

2 Emissions

# Removing biomass emissions, and aggregating according to sector
emi <- getQuery(prj, query = "CO2 emissions by tech") %>%
  filter(region == "UK", year > 2000, year < 2075, sector != "biomass liquids", subsector != "biomass") %>%
  group_by(scenario, sector, year) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  mutate(sector = if_else(str_detect(sector, regex("enuse|process heat cement|oil refining|coal to liquids|gas to liquids", ignore_case = TRUE)), "Industry", sector)) %>%
  mutate(sector = if_else(str_detect(sector, regex("fsuse|cement", ignore_case = TRUE)), "IPPU", sector)) %>%
  mutate(sector = if_else(str_detect(sector, regex("resid|comm", ignore_case = TRUE)), "Building", sector)) %>%
  mutate(sector = if_else(str_detect(sector, regex("trn", ignore_case = TRUE)), "Transport", sector)) %>%
  mutate(sector = if_else(str_detect(sector, regex("electricity", ignore_case = TRUE)), "Power", sector)) %>%
  group_by(scenario, sector, year) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  group_by(scenario, year) %>%
  mutate(percent = value / sum(value), percent = percent * 100) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(Unit = "MtCO2", value = value * 3.67)

3 Emission Intensity (MtCo2/GDP)

emi_tot <- emi %>%
  group_by(scenario, year) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  mutate(Unit = "MtCO2")

gdp_uk <- getQuery(prj, "GDP by region") %>%
  mutate(category = "GDP", value = value / 1000, Units = "billion1990USD") %>%
  filter(region == "UK", year > 2000) %>%
  mutate(value = 1.98 * value) %>%
  mutate(Units = "billion2020USD")

ei <- left_join(emi_tot, gdp_uk, by = c("year", "scenario")) %>%
  mutate(EmIntes = value.x / value.y) %>%
  mutate(EmIntes_2015 = ((EmIntes - 0.22) / 0.22) * 100)



ggplot() +
  geom_line(
    data = ei %>% filter(year > 2015),
    mapping = aes(x = year, y = EmIntes, color = scenario),
    size = 1.2
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = my_custom_palette[c(4, 6)]) +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 12),
    legend.title = element_blank(),
    legend.position = "top",
    legend.justification = c(0, 1)
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "",
    y = expression("Emission Intensity (MtCO"[2] * "/GDP"[italic("2020 USD billion")] * ")")
  ) # Use expression() with subscript

ggsave("output_plots/emission_intensity_of_gdp.png",
  device = "png", dpi = "print",
  width = 7, height = 5
)

writexl::write_xlsx(x = ei, "output_data/emission_intensity_of_gdp.xlsx")

4 Emission intensity of Energy (MtCo2/EJ)

fe3 <- getQuery(prj, "final energy consumption by aggregate sector and fuel") %>%
  filter(region == "UK", year > 2000) %>%
  group_by(scenario, sector, year) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  ungroup()

fe3 <- fe3 %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2020 & sector == "Building", value - 0.021782875, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2025 & sector == "Building", value - 0.020350346, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2030 & sector == "Building", value - 0.009090333, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2035 & sector == "Building", value - 0.004640063, value))


fe3 <- fe3 %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = sector, values_from = value) %>%
  mutate(`Industry` = `Industry` - `Agriculture`) %>%
  select(-Agriculture) %>%
  pivot_longer(3:6, names_to = "sector", values_to = "value")

energy_intensity <- left_join(fe3, emi, by = c("scenario", "year", "sector")) %>%
  filter(year > 2005) %>%
  mutate(eni = value.y / value.x)

writexl::write_xlsx(energy_intensity, "output_data/emission_intensity_of_energy.xlsx")

energy_intensity_indus <- energy_intensity %>%
  select(scenario, year, sector, eni) %>%
  filter(year > 2010, sector == "Industry") %>%
  mutate(eni2 = ((eni - 39.95) / 39.95) * 100)

#######################
ggplot() +
  geom_line(energy_intensity %>% filter(year > 2015, sector == "Industry"), mapping = aes(x = year, y = eni, linetype = scenario, color = sector)) +
  theme_pander(boxes = T, base_size = 14) +
  scale_fill_aaas() +
  labs(y = "Emission intensity of energy (MtCO2/EJ)", x = "")

7 Final Energy Consumption

fe <- getQuery(prj, "final energy consumption by sector and fuel") %>%
  filter(region == "UK", year > 2010) %>%
  mutate(input = gsub(x = input, pattern = "elect_td_res|elect_td_com|elect_td_bld", replacement = "electricity"))

fe <- fe %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2020 & input == "traditional biomass", value - 0.021782875, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2025 & input == "traditional biomass", value - 0.020350346, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2030 & input == "traditional biomass", value - 0.009090333, value)) %>%
  mutate(value = ifelse(year == 2035 & input == "traditional biomass", value - 0.004640063, value))

fe <- fe %>%
  group_by(scenario, input, year, Units) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(year, scenario) %>%
  mutate(percent = value / sum(value), percent = percent * 100)

fe_tot <- fe %>%
  select(-percent) %>%
  group_by(year, scenario, Units) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value))

writexl::write_xlsx(fe, "output_data/final_energy_by_fuel.xlsx")

fe$scenario <- factor(fe$scenario, levels = c("Reference", "Net_Zero"))
##################################

8 Transport

trans <- getQuery(prj, query = "transport service output by mode") %>%
  filter(region == "UK", year > 2010) %>%
  filter(!mode %in% c("LDV_2W", "LDV_4W", "LDV", "road")) %>%
  mutate(mode = mgsub::mgsub(mode,
    pattern = c("Air Domestic", "Air International", "Bus", "HSR", "LDV_3W", "Passenger Rail", "Cycle", "Walk"),
    replacement = c("Aviation", "Aviation", "Bus", "Rail", "3W", "Rail", "NMT", "NMT")
  )) %>%
  mutate(category = if_else(mode %in% c("2W", "3W", "4W", "Aviation", "Bus", "NMT", "Rail"), "Passenger", "Freight")) %>%
  group_by(scenario, year, mode, category, Units) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>%
  ungroup()

trans_tot <- trans %>%
  group_by(scenario, year, category, Units) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value))

writexl::write_xlsx(trans, "output_data/transport_service_demand.xlsx")
